pr_review_comment_body:
Don't misunderstand, I'm not angry or anything, especially not against you, I'm just curious about how the rules changed and I want to understand those rules in order to make my PRs in this objective and thus spend much less time on fixing philosophical stuff.

@ultrabug @tobes the documentation contains all the technical knowledge to create a well functioning module, and that's great. Maybe you should also consider writing a contribution manifest explaining for instance which conditions are needed in order to create a new module, your vision of module improvement, what is the general direction of the project, what are the good practices...
I know that a little of this info is spread in the whole *writing custom py3status modules* section, but I really think that those "philosophical" considerations should have their own subsection, or even their own entire section.

Only need to check `start_date` once:
```
if self.start_date:
    if self.end_date:
        return self.start_date <= now < self.end_date
    else: 
        return self.start_date <= now

Do you still see the slowdown if you load this eagerly in a static block?
```
private static Class<?> suiteClass = null;
static {
  suiteClass = Class.forName("org.scalatest.Suite", true, clazz.getClassLoader());
};
```
